# Orbit Axis :: files that must never be uploaded to Vercel (Update 4.0.3).
#
# Everything listed here is either private, local-only, or useless to a
# deployment. Keeping the upload small is a side benefit; the point is that
# private notes and local database state never leave this machine.
#
# .env.local is already excluded by Vercel (it never uploads dotenv files) and
# by .gitignore, and is listed again here so the intent is explicit.

# ── Secrets and local environment ──
# Deliberately a single wildcard: nothing whose name begins with ".env" reaches
# a deployment, including the placeholder-only *.example templates. They are
# harmless but useless there, and one absolute rule is easier to audit than a
# list of exceptions. Enforced by test/deployment-packaging.test.js.
.env*

# ── Local Vercel metadata (Update 4.0.4.2) ──
# `vercel link` and `vercel pull` write the linked project's id, org id, and
# downloaded environment values here, plus local build output. None of it is
# Orbit source and none of it belongs in an upload. One directory rule covers
# project.json, README.txt, .env.*.local, and output/ — individual file rules
# would be redundant and would rot as the CLI adds files.
.vercel/

# ── Obsidian vault and private project notes ──
07 Orbit App/
docs/
prompts/
.orbit/

# ── Local Supabase stack: config, migrations, seeds, CLI state ──
# Migrations are applied by the owner with the Supabase CLI, never by the app.
supabase/

# ── Tests and fixtures ──
test/

# ── Platform runtimes that a Linux function cannot use (Update 4.0.4) ──
# Vercel functions are Linux x64. The macOS executable is ~820 KB of dead
# weight there, and shipping a binary for another operating system into a
# public deployment is exactly the kind of thing that should be deliberate.
# lib/astro/bin/linux-x64/ and lib/astro/ephe/ are NOT excluded — they are
# force-included by "includeFiles" in vercel.json, because they are opened by
# path at runtime and so are invisible to Vercel's import tracing.
vendor/orbit-axis-engine/bin/darwin-arm64/

# ── Development tooling ──
.claude/
.github/

# ── Local build/tooling noise ──
node_modules/
*.log
.DS_Store
DESIGN_SYSTEM.md
